<title>HONG KONG: Pearl Oriental interim net up 81.9 pct.</title>
<headline>Pearl Oriental interim net up 81.9 pct.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1996-08-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months ended June 30</p>
<p>(in million HK$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (H.K. cents)	   9.1	   vs 6.0 (adjusted)</p>
<p>    Dividend (H.K. cents)    4.0	   vs 2.7 (adjusted)</p>
<p>    Exceptional items	  245.42 gain vs nil</p>
<p>    Net			    393.64	vs 216.37</p>
<p>    Turnover		     815.15	vs 1,007.38</p>
<p>    Company name		 Pearl Oriental Holdings</p>
<p>Ltd</p>
<p>    Books close		  September 19-23</p>
<p>    Dividend payable	   September 27</p>
<p>NOTE - Pearl Oriental engages in commercial property trading and development, project management, hotel management and consultancy services.</p>
<p>Net is after an exceptional gain on forfeiture of deposits from pre-sale of properties.</p>
<p>Comparative share earnings and interim dividend have been adjusted for the bonus issue in April 1996.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6368</p>
</text>
